            <title>[HBASE-3879] Add way to control the split position of region</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-3879</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently the split point picked to be the mid key of the HFile. &lt;br/&gt;
From the code comments: &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&quot;Midkey for this file.  We work with block boundaries only so&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;returned midkey is an approximation only.&quot;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;It could be good to have a way to override the default option and use other method.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Possible implementation:&lt;br/&gt;
Create interface (similar to Hadoop&apos;s partitioner) that gets StoreFile / StoreFile.Reader and return the splitting point.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
